"title": "2078: Jesus Christ, sonship of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2078",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ is described as Son of David, Son of Man and Son of God. His sonship speaks of his divinity and humanity and is closely associated with his role as promised Messiah, suffering Saviour, risen Lord and coming judge and king. It also speaks of his intimate, obedient and unique relationship with his Father and of his mission to enable people to become children of God through faith in him.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as the Son of David</h2>\n<h3>He is physically descended from David</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:1\">MAT 1:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:2-Matt1:20\">MAT 1:2–1:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:27\">LUK 1:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:32\">LUK 1:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:4\">LUK 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:11\">LUK 2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:23-Luke3:38\">LUK 3:23–3:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:3\">ROM 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:8\">2TI 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:16\">REV 22:16</a></p>\n<h3>He is the promised royal Messiah of David's line</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa16:5\">ISA 16:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:12-2Sam7:16\">2SA 7:12–7:16</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:11-1Chr17:14\">1CH 17:11–17:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:1-Ps89:4\">PSA 89:1–89:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:11\">PSA 132:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:17\">PSA 132:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:7\">ISA 9:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:1\">ISA 11:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:5-Jer23:6\">JER 23:5–23:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:15-Jer33:16\">JER 33:15–33:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:23-Ezek34:24\">EZK 34:23–34:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:24-Ezek37:25\">EZK 37:24–37:25</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:8\">ZEC 3:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech6:12\">ZEC 6:12</a></p>\n<h3>He is both the Son and Lord of David</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:41-Matt22:45\">MAT 22:41–22:45</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:35-Mark12:37\">MRK 12:35–12:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:41-Luke20:44\">LUK 20:41–20:44</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:1\">PSA 110:1</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as the Son of Man</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:10\">MRK 2:10</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:6\">MAT 9:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:24\">LUK 5:24</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:13\">JHN 3:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:13-Dan7:14\">DAN 7:13–7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:28\">MRK 2:28</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:8\">MAT 12:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:5\">LUK 6:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:51\">JHN 1:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:27\">JHN 6:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:28\">JHN 8:28</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as the Son of God</h2>\n<h3>His divine origin and divinity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:32-Luke1:35\">LUK 1:32–1:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:13\">JHN 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:18\">JHN 1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:18\">JHN 5:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:5\">JHN 17:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:24\">JHN 17:24</a></p>\n<h3>His intimate relationship with the Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:36\">MRK 14:36</a></strong> <em>“Abba” was a term of intimacy and familiarity that children used with their own fathers.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:17\">MAT 3:17</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:11\">MRK 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:22\">LUK 3:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:49\">LUK 2:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:18\">JHN 1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:32-John1:34\">JHN 1:32–1:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:35\">JHN 3:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:20\">JHN 5:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:38\">JHN 8:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:31\">JHN 14:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:23\">JHN 17:23</a></p>\n<h3>His knowledge of the Father's will</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:25-Matt11:27\">MAT 11:25–11:27</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:21-Luke10:22\">LUK 10:21–10:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:45-John6:46\">JHN 6:45–6:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:55\">JHN 8:55</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:13-John14:16\">JHN 14:13–14:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:15\">JHN 15:15</a></p>\n<h3>His obedience to the Father's mission</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:42\">MAT 26:42</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:36\">MRK 14:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:42\">LUK 22:42</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:13-Matt3:17\">MAT 3:13–3:17</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:9-Mark1:11\">MRK 1:9–1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:21-Luke3:22\">LUK 3:21–3:22</a> <em>His baptism</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:1-Matt4:11\">MAT 4:1–4:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:1-Luke4:13\">LUK 4:1–4:13</a> <em>His temptation</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:50\">MAT 12:50</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:17\">JHN 3:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:55\">JHN 8:55</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:17\">JHN 10:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:36\">JHN 10:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:31\">JHN 14:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:8\">JHN 17:8</a></p>\n<h3>His sharing in the Father's work</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:34\">JHN 3:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:34\">JHN 4:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:17\">JHN 5:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:21-John5:26\">JHN 5:21–5:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:40\">JHN 6:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:16\">JHN 8:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:4\">JHN 9:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:49-John12:50\">JHN 12:49–12:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:11\">JHN 14:11</a></p>\n<h3>His role as promised Messiah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:16\">MAT 16:16</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:20\">LUK 9:20</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:12-2Sam7:14\">2SA 7:12–7:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:11-1Chr17:13\">1CH 17:11–17:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:26-Ps89:27\">PSA 89:26–89:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:6-Isa9:7\">ISA 9:6–9:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:23\">MAT 1:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:14\">ISA 7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:15\">MAT 2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:1\">HOS 11:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:63-Matt26:64\">MAT 26:63–26:64</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:61-Mark14:62\">MRK 14:61–14:62</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:70\">LUK 22:70</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:41\">LUK 4:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:29-Luke22:30\">LUK 22:29–22:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:49\">JHN 1:49</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:27\">JHN 11:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:31\">JHN 20:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:33\">ACT 13:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:5\">HEB 1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:5\">HEB 5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:7\">PSA 2:7</a></p>\n<h3>His sharing the Father's character and being</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:3\">HEB 1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:26\">JHN 5:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:57\">JHN 6:57</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:30\">JHN 10:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:5\">JHN 17:5</a></p>\n<h3>The uniqueness of his sonship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:16\">JHN 3:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:18\">JHN 1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:18\">JHN 3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:3\">HEB 1:3</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's disciples become children of God through him</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4-Gal4:7\">GAL 4:4–4:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:50\">MAT 12:50</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:16-John3:18\">JHN 3:16–3:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:23-John5:24\">JHN 5:23–5:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:40\">JHN 6:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:26-John11:27\">JHN 11:26–11:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:1-John14:2\">JHN 14:1–14:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:31\">JHN 20:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:13-Rom8:17\">ROM 8:13–8:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:5-Eph1:6\">EPH 1:5–1:6</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as the son of natural parents</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:16\">MAT 1:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:25\">MAT 1:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:55\">MAT 13:55</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:3\">MRK 6:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:7\">LUK 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:48\">LUK 2:48</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:23\">LUK 3:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:22\">LUK 4:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:45\">JHN 1:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:42\">JHN 6:42</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:14\">ACT 1:14</a></p>",
